Rating: 4
Very tasty. Served it with grilled chicken, mushroom sauce, carrots, and asparagus. I followed the recipe exactly and the results were top-shelf. One caution (this was my error not the recipe's) - I used a ricer for the mash, but slightly undercooked the potatoes. This is OK when using a masher as it gives good texture, but with a ricer it leaves the final product with a "grainy" feel. It wasn't a disaster, but next time I'd make sure the potatoes are just a little on the overcooked side if I'm going to use the ricer. Again, this was my fault not the recipe's. Overall this was excellent, would definitely make it again. Keeps well in the fridge overnight also.

Rating: 4
I made this for a dinner party and it was gone FAST. My very picky husband loved it and so did I. It's very, very good. Make sure you cook the potatoes long enough so they are easy to mash, though. I wouldn't change a thing about the recipe.

Rating: 3
